        "created_at": "2018-08-11T10:39:58.147Z",
        "cooked": "<p>In the Java bindings, what is the correct usage of the Database object in terms of opening and closing it?</p>\n<p>The class scheduler example does fdb.open() once, and uses it for the whole example. Some third party examples I\u2019ve seen open/close it once per operation (I assume this is expensive).</p>\n<p>If my app only opens it once, is it capable of handling multiple concurrent requests? Does it reconnect itself if the connection dies? Or is this meant to be handled at the app level?</p>",
        "post_number": 1,
        "post_type": 1,
        "posts_count": 2,
        "updated_at": "2018-08-11T10:39:58.147Z",
        "reply_count": 0,
