        "created_at": "2018-08-13T16:32:55.477Z",
        "cooked": "<p>The recommended behavior is to keep a <code>Database</code> open and reuse it for as long as you need it. I don\u2019t think opening multiple <code>Databases</code> for the same cluster provides any advantages (unless you need to be able to set different database-level options), and opening them does have a cost, particularly if you are doing it for every transaction.</p>\n<p>A single <code>Database</code> will be able to handle multiple concurrent requests, and it will try to reconnect if a connection fails.</p>",
